transformation and action in spark


Apache Spark-- 
               distributed in-memory computing engine for large-scale data processing across clusters.
-Spark Driver (Master) → Manages everything, creates partitions
-Spark Executor (Worker) → Each partition processes alone on executor
  
-DATA COMES IN:--------100 Zomato servers receiving 1 crore orders per day (10GB data)
  
-Spark Driver (master node) does the partitioning based on input file size/splits 
  (default 128MB per partition) or based on user-specified numPartitions.
-PARTITION = Data split into chunks across servers (1 crore orders → 200 partitions sample example)


- TRANSFORMATIONS (The Plan) -  Instructions to modify data.
1=NARROW = 
Each partition is processed independently on ONE executor, NO data shuffle between partitions → FAST"  
    (map, filter, union)

2=WIDE = 
Partitions exchange data ACROSS executors via network (group by, join) → SLOW due to SHUFFLE"
  (group, join, sort, distinct)
  
3) ACTION = Spark waits to run ALL transformations until an ACTION is called (count, show, collect) 
  → This is LAZY EVALUATION"  
  
4) RDD: Resilient Distributed Dataset - 
  immutable, fault-tolerant collection of objects partitioned across cluster

Resilient   = Can recover from failures (recomputes lost partitions)
Immutable   = Cannot change once created (new RDD on transformation)
Fault-tolerant = Rebuilds lost data using lineage (DAG)
Partitioned = Split into chunks across cluster

## 3. SPARK HIERARCHY (How Jobs are Born)
1. Job: Created whenever an Action is called.
2. Stage: A Job is split into Stages at every Shuffle boundary (Wide Transformation).
3. Task: The smallest unit of work. One Task runs on one Partition of data.

