how to read json file in pyspark



1. What is json data and how to read it in spark?
ANS: JSON = text-based key-value semi-structured data. Read: spark.read.json("path")
MUST-KNOW: Use schema enforcement for performance; avoid inferSchema on large files.

2. What if I have 3 keys in all line and 4 keys in one line?
ANS: Spark adds 4th key as new column; missing keys become null.
MUST-KNOW: This is schema evolution; use .option("mergeSchema", "true") when writing.

3. What multiline and line-delimited json?
ANS: Multiline = one JSON across lines (multiLine=true). Line-delimited = one JSON per line (default).
MUST-KNOW: Line-delimited supports compression (gzip) and splitting; multiline needs whole file read.

4. Which one works faster - multiline or line-delimited?
ANS: Line-delimited (parallel split across files)
MUST-KNOW: Multiline kills parallelism because executor must read entire file; use only for nested/pretty-printed JSON.

5. How to convert nested json into spark dataframe?
ANS: Use from_json with schema OR .select("col.*") to flatten.
MUST-KNOW: explode() for arrays; to_json() for reverse; prefer explicit schema for nested structs.

6. What will happen if I have corrupted json file?
ANS: Spark puts bad records in _corrupt_record column when mode=PERMISSIVE.
MUST-KNOW: Use FAILFAST mode for quality checks; DROPMALFORMED to skip bad rows; handle via .filter("_corrupt_record is null")
